# Supabase credentials - same format as BeefiveApp
# Copy to .env and fill in your values from Supabase Dashboard > Settings > API
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.your-anon-key
#
# New / recreated project (CLI from repo root: cd bee_five):
#   supabase login
#   supabase link --project-ref YOUR_REF
#   supabase db push
#   supabase functions deploy submit-match
# Migrations live in bee_five/supabase/migrations/ (baseline 20260101000000 creates mg_* tables).

# Username-only signup uses a synthetic login on the server. In Dashboard >
# Authentication > Providers > Email: disable "Confirm email" so users are not
# blocked waiting for inbox verification after sign-up.
#
# In Supabase Dashboard > Authentication > URL Configuration, add Redirect URLs:
#   bee-five://confirm-email
#   bee-five://reset-password

# For "Forgot password" (recovery): in Authentication > Email Templates > "Reset password",
# add the 6-digit code so users can enter it in the app, e.g.:
#   Your reset code is: {{ .Token }}
# (The app uses this code so you never leave the app to reset your password.)
